# Commits and output: no branding or advertising

1. **Git commits** — Do not add `Co-authored-by:` trailers, “Generated with …”, tool names, or any attribution to Cursor, cursor-agent, or other AI/agent products. Write messages as a human maintainer would: what changed and why, nothing promotional.

2. **PR / changelog text** — Same rule: no tool plugs, no “this PR was created by …”, no affiliate-style mentions.

3. **General agent output** — Do not advertise Cursor or any product; do not append signatures, footers, or boilerplate that promotes a tool or service. Stay task-focused.

**Examples**

```text
❌ BAD commit body
Co-authored-by: Cursor <noreply@cursor.com>
🤖 Generated with Cursor

✅ GOOD commit body
Fix map test flake by waiting for MapContainer after POIs load.
```

If the user explicitly asks for a specific attribution line, follow their instruction; otherwise omit all of the above.
